00:11:20.320 --> 00:11:22.850
It's also important that they 
can be easily distinguished 

249
00:11:22.850 --> 00:11:23.993
from similar elements 
around them. 

250
00:11:23.993 --> 00:11:29.839
For example, linked embedded 
in the text paragraph.

251
00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:31.500
The need to 
see things clearly, 

252
00:11:31.500 --> 00:11:33.618
is shared among people 
who rely on their eyes 

253
00:11:33.618 --> 00:11:35.246
but the challenges 
are quite diverse. 

254
00:11:35.246 --> 00:11:36.817
People with visual impairment 

255
00:11:36.817 --> 00:11:38.876
might not be able 
to see certain colors. 

256
00:11:38.876 --> 00:11:41.466
Their field of view might be 
blurred or narrow. 

257
00:11:41.466 --> 00:11:44.320
It's also possible that the 
challenge is caused by the

258
00:11:44.320 --> 00:11:45.947
projection of light 
in the room

259
00:11:45.947 --> 00:11:47.920
or direct sunlight 
shining in the screen.

260
00:11:47.920 --> 00:11:50.171
The visual contrasts
between a color is 

261
00:11:50.171 --> 00:11:52.591
a key factor in making 
things perceivable 

262
00:11:52.591 --> 00:11:54.800
but color contrast 
has its limitations.

263
00:11:54.800 --> 00:11:57.006
Creating robust visual 
differences between elements 

264
00:11:57.006 --> 00:11:59.987
often requires a more 
holistic approach. 

265
00:11:59.987 --> 00:12:01.824
When I'm talking about 
holistic approaches, 

266
00:12:01.824 --> 00:12:03.232
it doesn't only have
to do with colors. 

267
00:12:03.232 --> 00:12:06.039
It's things like arrangement,
additional labeling, 

268
00:12:06.039 --> 00:12:10.048
spacing, like white space, 
content consistency. 

269
00:12:10.048 --> 00:12:12.959
Consistency is a big 
factor in accessibility.

270
00:12:12.959 --> 00:12:19.200
All help make the content 
distinguishable on the website.

271
00:12:20.480 --> 00:12:23.154
We're going to go into 
colors and contrast for text. 

272
00:12:23.154 --> 00:12:25.128
Providing sufficient contrast 

273
00:12:25.128 --> 00:12:27.292
between foreground 
and background. 

274
00:12:27.292 --> 00:12:29.839
For relevant luminance, 
the tone of a color,

275
00:12:29.839 --> 00:12:32.985
whether it's red, 
green, blue, yellow, 

276
00:12:32.985 --> 00:12:34.480
is not a key factor.

277
00:12:34.480 --> 00:12:36.949
After all, adequate contrast
is necessary for people 

278
00:12:36.949 --> 00:12:38.825
who can't perceive 
certain colors 

279
00:12:38.825 --> 00:12:40.540
or who don't see 
colors at all. 

280
00:12:40.540 --> 00:12:42.399
This means visually 
distinct colors

281
00:12:42.399 --> 00:12:45.360
don't automatically have
a high contrast ratio

282
00:12:45.360 --> 00:12:47.767
sometimes designers ask me
what's the best colors to use. 

283
00:12:47.767 --> 00:12:49.626
It's not always about
the best colors 

284
00:12:49.626 --> 00:12:51.897
It's about the contrast ratio 
of these colors. 

285
00:12:51.897 --> 00:12:53.463
While visually 
non-impaired users 

286
00:12:53.463 --> 00:12:54.594
might be able 
to perceive 

287
00:12:54.594 --> 00:12:57.537
the red and green words 
on the blue background, 

288
00:12:57.537 --> 00:12:58.957
for the image 
on the left, 

289
00:12:58.957 --> 00:13:00.692
others will have 
a very hard time

290
00:13:00.692 --> 00:13:03.290
differentiating between the
text and the background. 

291
00:13:03.290 --> 00:13:05.473
The image on the right 
is how it might look 

292
00:13:05.473 --> 00:13:06.872
to somebody who 
sees grayscale, 

293
00:13:06.872 --> 00:13:08.859
which you can see 
is very hard to distinguish 

294
00:13:08.859 --> 00:13:12.320
even for me, as someone 
who can see.

295
00:13:14.720 --> 00:13:17.768
To continue on this color 
and contrast for text, 

296
00:13:17.768 --> 00:13:20.409
to meet these standards, 
text should have 

297
00:13:20.409 --> 00:13:23.730
a color contrast ratio
of 4.5:1. 

298
00:13:23.730 --> 00:13:26.488
This ensures that viewers 
who cannot see 

299
00:13:26.488 --> 00:13:29.967
a full color spectrum, 
are able to read the text. 

300
00:13:29.967 --> 00:13:31.839
This also depends on 
the size of the text,

301
00:13:31.839 --> 00:13:34.993
text color, background, 
will determine if it 

302
00:13:34.993 --> 00:13:36.639
meets these requirements.

303
00:13:36.639 --> 00:13:39.803
To understand 
contrast ratio, 

304
00:13:39.803 --> 00:13:41.440
1:1 is the lowest 
contrast ratio.

305
00:13:41.440 --> 00:13:44.399
It means there's no difference 
between the colors.

306
00:13:44.399 --> 00:13:48.941
21:1 is the highest 
possible contrast ratio, 

307
00:13:48.941 --> 00:13:51.691
kind of like white text 
on a black background.

308
00:13:51.691 --> 00:13:54.102
While the highest contrast 
is generally good, 

309
00:13:54.102 --> 00:13:55.550
higher is not 
always better. 

310
00:13:55.550 --> 00:13:58.240
Research indicates
that moderate contrast,

311
00:13:58.240 --> 00:14:01.360
somewhere between 
the extremes is the best.

312
00:14:01.360 --> 00:14:03.550
Just using black and white
to reach a higher contrast 

313
00:14:03.550 --> 00:14:05.758
is not good 
for all users. 

314
00:14:05.758 --> 00:14:09.680
This is where 
the conversation 

315
00:14:09.680 --> 00:14:11.360
needs to come in for 
branding for projects.

316
00:14:11.360 --> 00:14:12.961
It can start 
with branding. 

317
00:14:12.961 --> 00:14:15.944
I've had hard conversations 
with companies on their 

318
00:14:15.944 --> 00:14:18.026
branding, colors, and 
what that means 

319
00:14:18.026 --> 00:14:21.801
when translating 
to the web. 

320
00:14:21.801 --> 00:14:24.857
If you diagnose a lot 
of websites out there 

321
00:14:24.857 --> 00:14:26.553
for accessibility, 
you come to find out 

322
00:14:26.553 --> 00:14:28.847
color contrast is 
probably one of the 

323
00:14:28.847 --> 00:14:30.425
biggest hurdles to tackle 

324
00:14:30.425 --> 00:14:32.870
and hardest for designers 
to keep things. 

325
00:14:32.870 --> 00:14:34.947
They're worried about 
being pretty 

326
00:14:34.947 --> 00:14:37.077
and aesthetically pleasing 
but there's a lot of techniques 

327
00:14:37.077 --> 00:14:40.399
you can use to 
get around that.

328
00:14:42.079 --> 00:14:44.376
Moving on from text,
we're going to do 

329
00:14:44.376 --> 00:14:47.952
color contrast for 
user interface components. 

330
00:14:47.952 --> 00:14:51.305
Version 2.1 of web
accessibility guidelines. 

331
00:14:51.305 --> 00:14:53.234
Minimal contrast 
is 3:1 contrast 

332
00:14:53.234 --> 00:14:56.480
[against] adjacent colors 
for all UI components.

333
00:14:56.480 --> 00:14:58.480
We're going to start 
with a bad example.

334
00:14:58.480 --> 00:15:00.583
In this one, the borders
of the input fields 

335
00:15:00.583 --> 00:15:03.397
have insufficient 
contrast ratio: 1.5:1. 

336
00:15:03.397 --> 00:15:04.567
Because of that, 
certain users 

337
00:15:04.567 --> 00:15:08.000
may have a hard time 
finding input fields to enter. 

338
00:15:08.000 --> 00:15:09.862
The background color, 
the send message button, 

339
00:15:09.862 --> 00:15:12.525
also has a low contrast ratio: 
1.5:1. 

340
00:15:12.525 --> 00:15:13.600
This will make it 
harder for users

341
00:15:13.600 --> 00:15:16.800
to identify the button.

342
00:15:19.440 --> 00:15:22.182
We'll continue on 
some more UI examples. 

343
00:15:22.182 --> 00:15:25.627
Form A versus Form B. 
Form B, on the right, 

344
00:15:25.627 --> 00:15:28.391
is saying, "Hey this is
aesthetically pleasing.

345
00:15:28.391 --> 00:15:29.600
This is what I like."

346
00:15:29.600 --> 00:15:33.680
Form B [with] a little higher contrast 
[would be] a lot more accessible.

347
00:15:33.680 --> 00:15:37.359
Borders, bolder text, bolder 
labeling text, things like that 

348
00:15:37.359 --> 00:15:40.089
make Form A much more 
accessible than Form B 

349
00:15:40.089 --> 00:15:44.720
and that's a direct contrast
on the same type of form.

350
00:15:45.920 --> 00:15:48.463
This one, there's a lot 
of options here, 

351
00:15:48.463 --> 00:15:49.902
one through four,
but we're mostly 

