00:15:49.902 --> 00:15:53.161
going to talk about 
one and four, and the contrast.

353
00:15:53.161 --> 00:15:54.839
The worst option is 
obviously number one 

354
00:15:54.839 --> 00:15:57.161
in terms of accessibility. 
The best option is number four. 

355
00:15:57.161 --> 00:15:58.399
You can see here 
a couple things

356
00:15:58.399 --> 00:16:00.052
are happening in four. 

357
00:16:00.052 --> 00:16:03.227
There is the use of color, 
icons, and error messages 

358
00:16:03.227 --> 00:16:05.680
to help the user understand 
what's going on.

359
00:16:05.680 --> 00:16:08.216
Option 4 is a good example
of not just using color 

360
00:16:08.216 --> 00:16:09.360
to help their guider.

361
00:16:09.360 --> 00:16:13.688
It's got a lot of other things 
to help guide the user on this. 

362
00:16:13.688 --> 00:16:18.157
Forms in general: there
can be a bigger conversation. 

363
00:16:18.157 --> 00:16:19.767
Best practices, 
making forms accessible:

364
00:16:19.767 --> 00:16:23.232
I could have a whole presentation 
based on form accessibility. 

365
00:16:23.232 --> 00:16:24.563
Right now we're 
just going into 

366
00:16:24.563 --> 00:16:27.363
the visual aspects
as you can see on here 

367
00:16:27.363 --> 00:16:29.660
like visual labeling, 
proper understanding, 

368
00:16:29.660 --> 00:16:31.600
a proper heading structure 
in sections,

369
00:16:31.600 --> 00:16:34.720
clear warning indicators
like you see in Option 4.

370
00:16:34.720 --> 00:16:37.436
For this purpose, 
I want you to know 

371
00:16:37.436 --> 00:16:40.341
sometimes just 
how color is used 

372
00:16:40.341 --> 00:16:43.759
when using it in 
user interface elements.

373
00:16:44.959 --> 00:16:46.413
Here's a navigation example.

374
00:16:46.413 --> 00:16:50.330
Navigation A uses color 
to show "Shop", 

375
00:16:50.330 --> 00:16:52.325
you select on "Shop", 

376
00:16:52.325 --> 00:16:54.424
but what you see 
in Option B is what 

377
00:16:54.424 --> 00:16:56.800
a colorblind person 
