"The quick brown fox 
jumps over the lazy dog". 

498
00:22:06.317 --> 00:22:08.138
If the text is 
on the image, 

499
00:22:08.138 --> 00:22:09.613
you can put it in alt text. 

500
00:22:09.613 --> 00:22:12.073
It is a good practice 
if you do it that way 

501
00:22:12.073 --> 00:22:15.200
but I just avoid it 
all together.

502
00:22:16.400 --> 00:22:19.009
Accessible Navigation: 
Designers and developers 

503
00:22:19.009 --> 00:22:22.183
should consider both 
site-wide and page navigation. 

504
00:22:22.183 --> 00:22:23.646
In general provide 
multiple ways 

505
00:22:23.646 --> 00:22:25.984
to reach any page 
on the site. 

506
00:22:25.984 --> 00:22:28.438
Doing so allows users 
to choose whatever 

507
00:22:28.438 --> 00:22:31.210
way of finding pages 
is easiest for them. 

508
00:22:31.210 --> 00:22:33.866
Users with low vision
may find using search 

509
00:22:33.866 --> 00:22:36.330
easier than navigating 
through a large menu. 

510
00:22:36.330 --> 00:22:39.771
Users with cognitive impairments 
may prefer a table of contents, 

511
00:22:39.771 --> 00:22:44.480
or a sitemap over clicking
through many pages.

512
00:22:45.200 --> 00:22:49.834
A presentation earlier 
by Adam Berkowitz 

513
00:22:49.834 --> 00:22:52.125
about building accessible 
navigation first for search, 

514
00:22:52.125 --> 00:22:54.720
goes over accessible navigation 
in much more detail 

515
00:22:54.720 --> 00:22:57.142
than I'll go on in
this one today. 

516
00:22:57.142 --> 00:22:58.809
I would recommend to go back 
and listen to that presentation 

517
00:22:58.809 --> 00:23:00.960
on how to make the navigation
much more accessible.

518
00:23:00.960 --> 00:23:03.920
I want to give some tips 
to consider...

519
00:23:03.920 --> 00:23:07.557
my tips on it too as well. 

520
00:23:07.557 --> 00:23:08.386
One of my first tips is 

521
00:23:08.386 --> 00:23:10.212
using conventional 
locations for menus 

522
00:23:10.212 --> 00:23:12.320
such as across the top 
or along the left side.

523
00:23:12.320 --> 00:23:15.520
Don't come up with some
like crazy hidden menus or

524
00:23:15.520 --> 00:23:17.181
along the right is also
weird for people. 

525
00:23:17.181 --> 00:23:20.177
That's why I recommend 
the top or the left. 

526
00:23:20.177 --> 00:23:23.323
Providing generous sizes 
for clickable areas, 

527
00:23:23.323 --> 00:23:26.000
generally no smaller 
than 44px by 44px.

528
00:23:26.000 --> 00:23:30.078
Don't make it real tiny, 
hard to hit, hard to find. 

529
00:23:30.078 --> 00:23:34.080
Locate these kind of
links on the navigation.

530
00:23:34.080 --> 00:23:36.913
Providing clear styles for
hover of the current states, 

531
00:23:36.913 --> 00:23:38.494
also known as focus. 

532
00:23:38.494 --> 00:23:41.831
When it's on focus you know 
where the cursor is or 

533
00:23:41.831 --> 00:23:44.047
you know where, 
when you're tapping 

534
00:23:44.047 --> 00:23:46.047
the keys to navigate the site, 

535
00:23:46.047 --> 00:23:47.279
you know where you're at.

536
00:23:47.279 --> 00:23:49.305
Ensuring that menus 
are keyboard operable

537
00:23:49.305 --> 00:23:51.743
and focus states are 
never hidden from the users. 

538
00:23:51.743 --> 00:23:54.730
Same as what I said before 
but just reassuring 

539
00:23:54.730 --> 00:23:57.327
don't hide where 
they're navigating. 

540
00:23:57.327 --> 00:23:59.513
Avoid linking off-site 
when possible,

541
00:23:59.513 --> 00:24:02.735
unless properly marked 
by labels or ARIA labels. 

542
00:24:02.735 --> 00:24:06.125
using navigation landmarks 
for screen readers. 

543
00:24:06.125 --> 00:24:08.880
People go back and forth 
on this one.

544
00:24:08.880 --> 00:24:10.748
A lot of people have 
different ideas of how 

545
00:24:10.748 --> 00:24:13.756
to do this kind of markup. 
I'll go over a little bit of

546
00:24:13.756 --> 00:24:16.159
some examples here soon.

547
00:24:16.559 --> 00:24:18.738
Keyboard Accessibility: 
Keyboard accessibility is 

548
00:24:18.738 --> 00:24:20.773
one of the most important 
aspects of web accessibility. 

549
00:24:20.773 --> 00:24:23.098
Many users with 
motor disabilities 

550
00:24:23.098 --> 00:24:25.129
rely on a keyboard 
to navigate websites 

551
00:24:25.129 --> 00:24:26.159
in place of a mouse.

552
00:24:26.159 --> 00:24:28.576
I encourage you to 
try to navigate 

553
00:24:28.576 --> 00:24:31.185
any of your sites or 
if you're with a keyboard,

554
00:24:31.185 --> 00:24:33.183
encourage you to try it. 

555
00:24:33.183 --> 00:24:35.275
Use the Tab key 
to go forward. 

556
00:24:35.275 --> 00:24:38.540
Use Shift + Tab key 
to go backwards, backtrack. 

557
00:24:38.540 --> 00:24:39.948
Keep in mind, 
like we said earlier 

558
00:24:39.948 --> 00:24:43.366
people have temporary disabilities
that will have to use a keyboard 

559
00:24:43.366 --> 00:24:46.224
or later in life 
become disabled 

560
00:24:46.224 --> 00:24:48.807
and they need help 
using the keyboard 

561
00:24:48.807 --> 00:24:51.919
instead of the mouse 
and they prefer it.

562
00:24:52.720 --> 00:24:56.240
Skip Navigation and 
Keyboard Navigation:

563
00:24:56.240 --> 00:24:59.755
Skip links are internal
pages, links which 

564
00:24:59.755 --> 00:25:01.295
aid navigation around 
the current page. 

565
00:25:01.295 --> 00:25:03.740
Rather than navigating 
completely new pages, 

566
00:25:03.740 --> 00:25:05.760
they are mainly used 
by screen readers

567
00:25:05.760 --> 00:25:10.400
for bypassing or skipping over 
repetitive page content.

568
00:25:10.400 --> 00:25:12.775
When I heard about them first, 
I had no idea where they were 

569
00:25:12.775 --> 00:25:15.226
or how to figure them out. 
It took some time for me 

570
00:25:15.226 --> 00:25:18.000
to figure out how to use
proper skip link navigation.

571
00:25:18.000 --> 00:25:20.829
Skip links can conclude like,
you see in the example, 

572
00:25:20.829 --> 00:25:22.566
skip over primary navigation. 

573
00:25:22.566 --> 00:25:25.524
You can also have 
skip to main content, 

574
00:25:25.524 --> 00:25:28.649
skip to sidebar, skip to footer. 
I would keep it limited. 

575
00:25:28.649 --> 00:25:30.664
I wouldn't do 50 of them 
or something like that. 

576
00:25:30.664 --> 00:25:32.501
I would keep it to 
the main section of

577
00:25:32.501 --> 00:25:36.480
the content you want 
people to have access to.

578
00:25:37.120 --> 00:25:40.144
Focus Indicators: Can you tell,
and this is one the questions, 

579
00:25:40.144 --> 00:25:41.956
can you tell where 
the element is in focus 

580
00:25:41.956 --> 00:25:43.364
when they're using 
their keyboard? 

581
00:25:43.364 --> 00:25:45.600
Does the element stop 
moving when it's in focus?

582
00:25:45.600 --> 00:25:48.179
Elements can include 
text links, buttons, 

583
00:25:48.179 --> 00:25:49.919
forms, navigations, 
and sliders.

584
00:25:49.919 --> 00:25:53.295
All these elements, 
you want to have a way that, 

585
00:25:53.295 --> 00:25:57.840
hey this is what
you're focused on.

586
00:25:58.240 --> 00:26:00.108
We're going to go to
the demonstration part 

587
00:26:00.108 --> 00:26:02.000
of my project here.

588
00:26:02.000 --> 00:26:03.910
Let me see... 
switch over to... 

589
00:26:03.910 --> 00:26:07.170
I'm not picking on anybody 
when I'm demonstrating websites. 

590
00:26:07.170 --> 00:26:12.559
I'm just trying to show you 
how things work.

591
00:26:12.559 --> 00:26:15.489
When you hit the Tab key, 

592
00:26:15.489 --> 00:26:16.685
I'm gonna use Unilever 
as an example,

593
00:26:16.685 --> 00:26:20.000
they're a big company.

594
00:26:20.000 --> 00:26:22.080
The first thing you see is 
Skip to content.

595
00:26:22.080 --> 00:26:24.907
A user could 
hit enter on this 

